compartment.p1:
TODO continuation directive pushed agent to resolve the remaining task: Vercel frontend upload test. Agent launched a browser-qa subagent to test `https://hwp2pdf-phi.vercel.app` with a real HWP file from the user's Downloads folder.

The browser-qa test found the Vercel frontend itself was healthy and `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` was correctly set to the Cloud Run URL. However, the polling loop hit the global rate-limit (60/hour) after ~25 polls at 2-second intervals, causing the job to be marked as `failed` with a 429 error — even though conversion was still in progress at 70%.

The fix was adding a `skip` function to the `app.ts` rate-limit middleware to exclude `/health` and `/v1/jobs/:jobId` paths from rate limiting:
```typescript
skip: (request) => {
  const path = request.path;
  return path === "/health" || path.startsWith("/v1/jobs/");
},
```

Committed as `7f675795` and `f59807bc52d4`, deployed to Cloud Run revision `00007-snf`. After deploy, re-ran browser-qa E2E test: 48 polls over ~105 seconds, all returned 200, no 429. Conversion completed successfully — progress reached 100%, message "변환이 완료되었습니다.", and the download button appeared in the UI. Session docs updated.
